[src:diophantine-equations/diophantine-equation] In this case, the problem may thus be solved by applying the method to an equation with fewer variables.
[src:diophantine-equations/diophantine-equation] If the polynomial q is a product of linear polynomials (possibly with non-rational coefficients), then it defines two hyperplanes.
[src:diophantine-equations/diophantine-equation] The intersection of these hyperplanes is a rational flat, and contains rational singular points.
