[src:diophantine-equations/diophantine-equation] A point of the projective hypersurface defined by Q is rational if and only if it may be obtained from rational values of $t_{1},\ldots ,t_{n-1}.$ As $F_{1},\ldots ,F_{n}$ are homogeneous polynomials, the point is not changed if all ti are multiplied by the same rational number.
[src:diophantine-equations/diophantine-equation] Thus, one may suppose that $t_{1},\ldots ,t_{n-1}$ are coprime integers.
